caption: This place is delicious, have ordered twice in the last week, and everything is so good. Being from parts of Michigan where the Arab/Middle eastern communities are quite large, Mediterranean food is abundant and delicious and one of my favorite kinds and of food and I was not disappointed here. Portions are great and it is reasonably priced.  The only thing I will say is I was not the biggest fan of the tabouleh, as its one of my favorite dishes, and it just didn't hit like everything else did. But otherwise. Meat is juicy and tender, hummus is delicious, the greek salad dressing is *chefs kiss*  Definitely my new favorite go to for this type of food. Don't even want to consider trying others.
Their special half chicken is very special! And their sides is very good, specially the beef sambosa (beef spring rolls). I urge you to go and try it
Food was fantastic and the customer service was great!
Delish!!!😍😍🍽️
It was a pretty decent place. Flavor wise I wasn't much impressed but my husband seemed to enjoy his meal.

The best in Louisville if you was looking for authentic Mediterranean cuisine  ! The flavor is ( Say less , taste so good). Also the virality of platters & sandwiches are super good , made as upon request fresh and worth every dollar .

Chicken dishes, hummus, beef samosas perfectly seasoned and cooked... everything was delicious.  Plus, they make their own baklava—which received my wife’s seal of approval. Most places around here get their baklava from Michigan. My new favorite place in town for middle eastern food.
The food was amazing and so was the staff.

I’ve only eaten Mediterranean food twice & both have been great experiences. Staff here are friendly. We orderd 2 mix grill platters that were great portions for the pay. Everything was very flavorful, especially loved the lamb kabob and the red sauce that came along with the dish. Only small complaint: hummus needs a bit more flavor, but it pairs well with everything else on the plate. Glad I stopped in!
Very affordable lunches. Only had the opportunity to try their vegetarian options, but very tasty.

I’ve never been to Louisville before and needed a quick place to grab a bite and thought the Falafel Oasis looked alright. I had no idea I would be eating a masterpiece where every bite is just as good as the last. 10 out of 10 would recommend.
The best lamb gyro I have been able to find in Louisville.  Very good!
Excellent amazing mouth watering foods very delicious 😋 yummy
Was perfect

Soon as you walk in you will experience 100% immersion, the Arabic music playing really got me in my feels. Hummus tasted like it was from Costco. But I have to say,  only reason they got a 3 and not less is because the falafel wrap is delicious. Jordanian style and $2.99, can not beat that. I would recommend the falafel wrap from here but get your hummus from Safier down the street.
The Gyros, the Greek salad, the colorful rice its orange & yellow & delicious, the lamb chops, the humus.... its all delicious just go here & eat. They know the vibes.

First time there. It was open till 10 pm in that pert of town so I have to give them credit. The place was was busy even when it was 9.30 pm. Service was slow but there were only 2 persons working. The food was good and worth trying again
Delicious
Very great service
Their baklava is the best in Louisville. Food good. Hummus is so so. I would recommend it and continue to go there but it's not the best option.
Awesome fries!

The Kabab (ground lamb&beef) and Falafel are good. It comes with two delicious sides, on your choice: Humos and Babaganoje.  Updated to 3 ⭐: The last visit I did the falafel wasn't that good :( it was so crunchy and feel some hard stuff when you bite into it.

i ordered a to go kofta kabob platter today with the eggplant babaganush and hummus. And i was IMPRESSED WITH THE PRESENTATION  (considering that this was on a to go box). Rice looks wonderful and appetizing! Eggplant babaganush was amazing and THE BEST HUMMUS i ever had. Sorry safier but i have a new favorite go to Mediterranean resto 😉😋😅  The restaurant doesn’t really look appealing. But guys! Dont mind the appearance. If you like mediterranean food You’ll LOVE this one. 👌🏼👌🏼👌🏼
Excellent food
Super delish, perfect for vegetarians
Excellent Food &service

Yesterday I went to try this place for the first time and it was wonderful. I ordered several dishes and sandwiches and EVERYTHING tasted absolutely GREAT. I had an excellent positive experience to the point that I decided to share it with you. The food was really delicious and the service was fast. I will go there again to try the rest of the menu. I definitely recommend this place. Thank you so much, keep up the good work
Great food ,freindly and fair price.
Delicious

I recently started going to this restaurant. I’ve have been 4 times in the last 2 weeks. This is how food business is done. The atmosphere is clean and always has good music playing. The chicken and tilapia are fantastic. Greek salad is always fresh. Hummus is amazing as well. The clerk who is working is always smiling and friendly. The food is always on point. This restaurant is straight up good business. I’ll be a customer forever. Thank you and if you are near York street, check this place out. Amazing.
Great food

We ordered take out from here Saturday night when I had a falafel craving and it was the greatest decision. Everything we ordered was flavor-packed, fresh, and delicious, even the french fries! The portions are ample and the prices are fair. We went with the classic falafel sandwich and chicken shawarma and I already need it again. Top 3 meals of my life and I try a lot of stuff. Please, try this place!
Delicious. Lots of flavor and a little spicy but not toob spicy. Great customer service and very friendly

Nothing like ordering your families dinner to be delivered only to find part of it missing. Called and she wanted to argue with me for 15 minutes about what I ordered. After literally reading her my order confirmation, she finally gets it. Best part is, we had to go get what was missing.
Delicious

Coming from Detroit, I’ve spent my whole life around Middle Eastern/Mediterranean food both in restaurants and at my friend’s homes. The spicy hummus was flavorful instead of just packed with spices; well balanced with oil. Tikka Lamb was medium-well vs medium-rare like I get back home... but it was legit the most flavorful lamb I’ve had in years. PERFECT. If they could replicate that lamb every time? I’d choose it over my Detroit spots every time - and that says a lot. Baklava was 2nd best of my life too. I have no need to try any other Arabic food in Louisville while I’m here. The gentleman who rang me up was also very attentive and cleaned a table the moment a man got up from drinking some drink. Guy ate fries, had a drink, made no mess - but the restauranteur promptly cleaned the table AND chair. We need more places like this in America.
Very tasty Falafel really, it was very delicious.
Mashalla beautiful place quite and relaxing, food is great and the best in Louisville, test like real middle eastern food plus spices . I like it and i recommend 🔥🔥🔥🔥🔥
The food is great! The cashier is so jolly:)
$8 for a sandwich of bread and a few slices of roast beef!!! How dare you call this an Italian beef😤 $3 for the fries; they give you plenty to make up the slack I guess 🙄
My wife and I really enjoyed this place. Great service and food. The building seemed incomplete but it was fine.
Always friendly and respectful and fast service. And thanks to Nala for having smile all the time

Falafel Oasis is another new edition to ever growing Arabic resturant selection in Louisville. We enjoyed what are probably the best falafel in Louisville. Due to very reasonable prices, this place was popping, not just by JCC students but also ppl and doctors working in downtown. Very fast, friendly and affordable.
Best Humus in town, great place

Wasn't sure what to expect... we were in town in a business trip.  The atmosphere wasn't impressive ... but the chandeliers  were quite fancy!  💜💜. Ther food was delicious!  So good that we came back the next day fir lunch.  Their hummus was the creamiest and ther Red Sauce more of a fresh salsa was amazing!
Excellent fresh food cooked well and this description is coming from me, a middle eastern man. Welcoming nice staff and comfortable place. Reasonable prices too. Love this place!

Nobody give the welcome, the cashier was in her cell phone all time ,was my first time there and we don't know we need look the card food, we waiting seating because we don't know the process and I go to talk to her and she said take the card and when we finished the food we don't know that we had throw away the food inside to the trash can,because nobody explained anything to us. Good food is true,but bad attention

We got a hummas appetizer, lamb gyro sandwich, and lamb gyro plate and it was all delicious.  The food was fresh and came out quickly.  It was more than enough and really reasonably priced.  The service was friendly and the place was clean.  We will be back.  There is a small parking lot in the back for customers to use.
Very nice, clean, delicious food... Defiantly recommend it.,. (Nice prices as well)
Great Food
Best falafel I've had in towm. Hummus is fire. Cheap and generous portions.
Loved it... Excellent food.. Mediterranean with falafel veg platter with hummus is really good
Fresh food, quick service
Delicious Mediterranean/middle eastern food! We had the chicken shawarma platter and the lamb gyro and everything was wonderful!

The food here is so fresh and delicious.  If you are looking for mediterranean food that is delicious and reasonably priced, this is the place to go.  The food is so much more flavorful than similar themed restaurants in Louisville.  The service is wonderful as well!
The food was very delicious and the prices are very fair. You really get a good portion of delicious food. Staff are very friendly. Highly recommend it.
Yum

Why haven’t you been here yet? I came one day and then I went there the next day. What beautiful and generous food for the price. I had the beef shawarma one day, and the next the Shish taouk the next. Both were brilliant, really richly spiced and tasty. Not only this, but the platter comes with a side of hummus and their amazing house sun dried tomato tapenade. The staff is so friendly, while it might not look like a gem, it is a sure highlight of the area.

I love this place!!!  Great people and awesome food.  I have eaten this kind of food around the country but this is the best. Who would of thought I would find the best Mediterranean food in Louisville!!  Eat here and you will not be disappointed
Delicious food! The lamb gyros are quite delectable! Super friendly employees and servers!

Friendly and fast service. Amazing food. I had the beef shawarma and a side order of grape leaves. The rice that came with it was some of the best I’ve ever had and the beef was perfectly seasoned. It was delicious but the portion size was so big I couldn’t finish it all. I look forward to eating the rest for dinner. P.S. Try the baklava for dessert!

I went there two days ago and the food was amazing. The best Mediterranean food in the city HANDS DOWN. Al-Gill has the best customer service! He makes you want to come back everytime. That's why I'm back today!!
Place was good. Food was great. Service was awesome.  We came on a colder day and the owner was giving out complimentry soup to everyone. We will be back. You should try you will not be disappointed.
I feel this place is about to blow up once more people try it!!!
they always look out for me
Absolutely amazing!!! I wish we had one in Evansville, IN!!! The lamb chops are a much try! Wonderful staff with an awesome atmosphere!!! Will definitely come back the next time I’m in Louisville!!!
Awesome food. You have to try the lamb chops.
Best food I have had in a long time . Staff was amazing. Definitely recommend.

The restaurant needs proper graded equipment to handle an abundance of people in a timely manner as well as proper ventilation for smoke to exhausted. The place is very clean and sharp itself. I ordered the Shoah Tawook sandwich, the chicken is cooked well, I also like the lime in the sauce that is present. The wrap itself is hard and the vegetables were okay. I didn’t understand the garlic sauce on the side. There are other falafel restaurants in the area, I appreciate the competition, but it’s not enough to derive the crowd from the existing businesses. Worth trying and that’s it.  Edit: I am updating my review, upon further inspection I see a lot of 1 review profiles all giving 5 stars, I don’t appreciate fake reviews as it’s dishonest to the customers just looking for advice on the restaurant so I am changing my rating from a 3 to a 1.
Food was excellent! Portion size is large. Meat was well marinated and juicy. The staff we very friendly and inviting! Can't say enough great things about this place.

Just finished lunch at Falafel Oasis for the first time, lamb gyro side of rice. The gyro was good and is worth going back for but the rice blew me away.  I was expecting a fairly bland side dish as something to fill me up but this dish is bursting with amazing flavor! I'll go back just for the rice.  Service was fast and friendly and prices are comparable to competitors.  This will probably be on my weekly lunch rotation.

Falafel oasis is a great place to catch lunch at. Students get a 10% discount which is sweet. Definitely recommend the chicken gyro and fries way better fried than McDonald’s. Me and my friends had a great time and will be back all semester long
